  "body": "Geth was started like this:\r\n\r\ngeth --cache 4096 --rpc --rpcaddr 0.0.0.0 --rpccorsdomain chrome-extension://nkbihfbeogaeaoehlefnkodbefgpgknn,chrome-extension://nlbmnnijcnlegkjjpcfjclmcfggfefdm,https://myeth.mydomain.com --ws --wsaddr 0.0.0.0 --wsport 8547 --wsorigins '*'\r\n\r\nIt was already in sync with the main eth network.\r\n\r\nGeth stopped synching ( new tokens and eth balances were not showing up ) but I could still post transactions through it while this was happening.\r\n\r\nI went frenzy into ^C^C^C to stop it and upon restart it recovered just fine - synched the few blocks up to the latest block.\r\n\r\nThe last ^C produced a stacktrace which I'm attaching here as geth.log.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\ngeth.log\r\n\r\nVersion: 1.7.3-stable-4bb3c89d\r\nOS: Debian stretch kernel 4.9.0-5-amd64\r\n[geth.log](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/files/1711221/geth.log)\r\n",
